---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Alex Hagemeister — Portfolio"
  description="Portfolio of Alex Hagemeister. AI/ML infrastructure, RAG systems, and production-focused software."
  currentPath="/"
  showBrand={false}
>
  <main class="container">
    <header class="hero">
      <div class="hero-image">
        <img src="/images/profile.png" alt="Portrait of Alex Hagemeister" />
      </div>
      <div class="hero-content">
        <h1>Alex Hagemeister</h1>
        <p class="location">San Francisco</p>
        <p class="tagline">
          I build things. Most of them interesting, some of them useful.<span class="cursor">_</span>
        </p>
        <nav aria-label="External links" class="hero-links">
          <a href="mailto:hagemeister.alex@gmail.com">Email</a>
          <a
            href="https://github.com/AlexHagemeister"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noreferrer">GitHub</a
          >
          <a
            href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/alexhagemeister/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noreferrer">LinkedIn</a
          >
          <a
            href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2410.02680"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noreferrer">Research</a
          >
        </nav>
      </div>
    </header>

    <section id="about" class="reveal">
      <h2><span class="prefix">//</span> About</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>B.S. EECS, UC Berkeley, graduating May 2026.</strong> Regents' and
        Chancellor's Scholarship recipient.
      </p>

      <p>
        AI capability is accelerating faster than most can fully grasp, but most
        organizations are still figuring out how to use it for anything beyond
        chatbots and demo days. What AI can technically do will continue to
        outpace what companies and developers can actually get out of them.
      </p>

      <p>
        <strong>That gap is my target for the next 2-5 years:</strong> the infrastructure
        that takes raw AI capability and makes it work inside real workflows with
        messy data and vague requirements.
      </p>

      <p>
        Writing code is getting commoditized. <strong>What isn't:</strong> figuring
        out what needs to exist, designing the system that gets you there, and making
        it run reliably in production.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="projects">
      <h2><span class="prefix">//</span> Selected Work</h2>
      <div class="project reveal" style="transition-delay: 0ms">
        <div class="window-chrome"><span /><span /><span /></div>
        <h3><span class="prefix">&gt;</span> Highly Adaptive Ridge</h3>
        <p>
          Co-authored ML research paper as sole undergraduate in UC Berkeley's
          Center for Targeted Machine Learning. <a
            href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2410.02680"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noreferrer">arXiv:2410.02680</a
          >
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="project reveal" style="transition-delay: 80ms">
        <div class="window-chrome"><span /><span /><span /></div>
        <h3><span class="prefix">&gt;</span> SPLAT — AI Course Tutors, UC Berkeley</h3>
        <p>
          Lead developer on Berkeley-funded EdTech platform for course-specific
          AI tutors. Built the ingestion, retrieval, generation, and
          student-facing application layers.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="project reveal" style="transition-delay: 160ms">
        <div class="window-chrome"><span /><span /><span /></div>
        <h3><span class="prefix">&gt;</span> IT Service Desk Intern — Stanford Research Institute</h3>
        <p>
          Embedded technical support for SRI researchers, handling 300+ service
          requests in three months and unblocking teams when infrastructure
          failed.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="currently-building">
      <h2><span class="prefix">//</span> Currently Building</h2>
      <div class="project reveal" style="transition-delay: 0ms">
        <div class="window-chrome"><span /><span /><span /></div>
        <h3><span class="prefix">&gt;</span> MCP Servers — Workflow Automation</h3>
        <p>
          Production Model Context Protocol servers for automating knowledge
          work, including Gmail API integration, task workflows, and document
          processing.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="project reveal" style="transition-delay: 80ms">
        <div class="window-chrome"><span /><span /><span /></div>
        <h3><span class="prefix">&gt;</span> Cursor Memory System — Developer Tooling</h3>
        <p>
          A persistent memory architecture for AI-assisted development workflows
          focused on better context retrieval and long-term project awareness.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="background">
      <h2><span class="prefix">//</span> Background</h2>
      <ul class="background-list">
        <li class="reveal" style="transition-delay: 0ms">
          <span class="line-num">01</span>
          <strong>Burning Man installations.</strong> Led teams building large-scale
          art that burned.
        </li>
        <li class="reveal" style="transition-delay: 60ms">
          <span class="line-num">02</span>
          <strong>Off-grid infrastructure.</strong> Designed and managed complete
          field power/water systems.
        </li>
        <li class="reveal" style="transition-delay: 120ms">
          <span class="line-num">03</span>
          <strong>National touring band.</strong> Self-booked and self-managed touring
          logistics.
        </li>
        <li class="reveal" style="transition-delay: 180ms">
          <span class="line-num">04</span>
          <strong>Sushi chef.</strong> Self-taught, hired directly as chef, rapidly
          reached top certification tier.
        </li>
        <li class="reveal" style="transition-delay: 240ms">
          <span class="line-num">05</span>
          <strong>Khan Academy math sprint.</strong> Seven years of curriculum in
          six months.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* ── Terminal prefix ── */
  .prefix {
    color: var(--accent-cyan);
    margin-right: 8px;
  }

  /* ── Blinking cursor ── */
  .cursor {
    color: var(--accent-cyan);
    animation: blink 1s step-end infinite;
  }

  @keyframes blink {
    50% { opacity: 0; }
  }

  /* ── Hero ── */
  .hero {
    padding: 64px 0 42px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 42px;
  }

  .hero-image img {
    width: 192px;
    height: 192px;
    object-fit: cover;
    border-radius: 50%;
  }

  h1 {
    font-family: "Playfair Display", serif;
    font-size: 2.45rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    margin: 0 0 8px;
  }

  .location {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    margin: 0 0 18px;
  }

  .tagline {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 1.15rem;
  }

  .hero-links {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 16px;
    margin-top: 18px;
  }

  .hero-links a {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    text-decoration: none;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
  }

  .hero-links a:hover {
    color: var(--accent-cyan);
  }

  /* ── Sections ── */
  section {
    padding: 36px 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  #about {
    border-top: none;
    padding-top: 0;
  }

  h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-style: normal;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    margin: 0 0 24px;
  }

  p {
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    margin: 0 0 18px;
  }

  /* ── Project cards ── */
  .window-chrome {
    display: flex;
    gap: 6px;
    margin-bottom: 14px;
  }

  .window-chrome span {
    width: 8px;
    height: 8px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--border);
    transition: background 150ms ease;
  }

  .project:hover .window-chrome span:nth-child(1) {
    background: #ec6a5e;
  }

  .project:hover .window-chrome span:nth-child(2) {
    background: #f4bf4f;
  }

  .project:hover .window-chrome span:nth-child(3) {
    background: #61c554;
  }

  .project {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 20px 24px;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    transition:
      border-color 150ms ease,
      opacity 0.4s ease,
      transform 0.4s ease;
  }

  .project:hover {
    border-color: var(--accent-cyan);
  }

  .project:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .project h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    margin: 0 0 8px;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--fg);
  }

  .project p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .project a {
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-color: transparent;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
    text-decoration-thickness: 1px;
  }

  .project a:hover {
    text-decoration-color: var(--accent);
  }

  /* ── Background list ── */
  .background-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 12px;
  }

  .line-num {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--accent-cyan);
    opacity: 0.5;
    margin-right: 14px;
    user-select: none;
  }

  .background-list li {
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    padding: 4px 0 4px 0;
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    border-left: 2px solid var(--border);
    padding-left: 16px;
    transition:
      border-color 150ms ease,
      opacity 0.4s ease,
      transform 0.4s ease;
  }

  .background-list li:hover {
    border-left-color: var(--accent-cyan);
  }

  .background-list li:hover .line-num {
    opacity: 1;
  }

  @media (max-width: 860px) {
    .hero {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: flex-start;
      padding-top: 48px;
      gap: 24px;
    }

    .hero-image img {
      width: 148px;
      height: 148px;
    }

    h1 {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }
  }
</style>
